<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="difficulty-n">difficulty <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'dɪfɪkəlti/    美 /'dɪfɪkəlti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 困难；艰难：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the difficulty of carrying out the work
开展工作的困难</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>have no difficulty with</strong> English grammar.
我在英语语法方面没有困难。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I learned <strong>with difﬁculty</strong> how to drive.
我好不容易才学会开车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We found the house <strong>without difﬁculty</strong>.
我们毫不费力地找到了那所房子。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>have difﬁculty (in) doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is not uncommon for students to have difficulty understanding classics.
学生理解名著有困难，这很常见。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 1</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] [常用复数] 难事；难题；困境：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>run into difficulties</strong>
遇到困难</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Parents should encourage their children to <strong>overcome difficulties</strong> and inspire them to develop by themselves.
父母应鼓励孩子克服困难，激励他们自我发展。</p><footer>2013 福建书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She soon <strong>ran / got into difﬁculties / difﬁculity</strong> with debt.
她很快陷入了债务困境。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bank is <strong>in difﬁculties / difﬁculty</strong>.
这家银行处境艰难。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-u">3.★ <strong>[U] 困难程度：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The tests vary <strong>in difficulty</strong>.
测试的难易程度有所不同。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>You can’t imagine what difficulty we had <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (walk) home in the snowstorm.  （2007 辽宁改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. walking  </p></div>